# Prefab and Asset Conventions

## Visual Library Pipeline

All prefabs are assigned via `UnitVisualLibrary` (ScriptableObject, `Insect Wars/Unit Visual Library`). The runtime falls back to **procedural placeholder geometry** when no prefab is provided — this is by design.

Prefab slots in `UnitVisualLibrary`:
- **Units:** `workerPrefab`, `meleePrefab`, `rangedPrefab`
- **Buildings:** `hivePrefab`, `undergroundPrefab`, `skyTowerPrefab`
- **Environment:** `rottingApplePrefab`, `calorieChunkPrefab`, `clayWallPrefab`, `bigAppleMaterial`, `groundMaterial`, `baseSoilLayer`, `drySoilLayer`
- **Terrain features:** `waterPuddlePrefab`, `tallGrassPrefab`, `mudPatchPrefab`, `thornPatchPrefab`, `rockyRidgePrefab`
- **Combat:** `projectilePrefab`

## Prefab Rules

- **Pivot** at ground level, center XZ
- **No colliders** — added programmatically (`NavMeshObstacle`, `BoxCollider`, `CapsuleCollider`)
- **No NavMeshObstacle/NavMeshModifier** — added by code
- **No MonoBehaviour scripts** on art prefabs
- **No lights or cameras**
- **Y rotation** is set by the system — don't bake rotation into prefabs
- Unit prefabs require `NavMeshAgent`, `CapsuleCollider`, `InsectUnit` on root (added if missing)

## Performance Budgets

- Terrain feature prefabs: **under 1500 triangles**
- **1–2 materials** per prefab (URP/Lit or URP/Simple Lit)
- Avoid transparency (use alpha-clip if needed for grass)
- No real-time lights, reflections, or heavy transparency
- Use LODs for complex meshes (rocky ridges)
- Static shared meshes/materials for selection rings, health bars

## Team Color Application

`TeamPalette` tinting is applied at spawn via `MaterialPropertyBlock` (prefabs) or material tint cache (procedural). Art prefabs should use a **neutral/white base color** so team tinting works correctly. The system sets `_BaseColor` or `_Color` on all renderers.
